   36  pub enum AnnNode<'a> {
   37      NodeBlock(&'a ast::Block),
   38      NodeItem(&'a ast::Item),
   39      NodeExpr(&'a ast::Expr),
   40      NodePat(&'a ast::Pat),
   41  }

   43  pub trait PpAnn {
   44      fn pre(&self, _state: &mut State, _node: AnnNode) -> IoResult<()> { Ok(()) }
   45      fn post(&self, _state: &mut State, _node: AnnNode) -> IoResult<()> { Ok(()) }
   46  }

   57  pub struct State<'a> {
   58      s: pp::Printer,
   59      cm: Option<&'a CodeMap>,
   60      intr: @token::IdentInterner,
   61      comments: Option<Vec<comments::Comment> >,
   62      literals: Option<Vec<comments::Literal> >,
   63      cur_cmnt_and_lit: CurrentCommentAndLiteral,
   64      boxes: RefCell<Vec<pp::Breaks> >,
   65      ann: &'a PpAnn
   66  }

   68  pub fn rust_printer(writer: ~io::Writer) -> State<'static> {
   69      static NO_ANN: NoAnn = NoAnn;
   70      rust_printer_annotated(writer, &NO_ANN)
   71  }
   72  
   73  pub fn rust_printer_annotated<'a>(writer: ~io::Writer,
   74                                    ann: &'a PpAnn) -> State<'a> {
   75      State {
   76          s: pp::mk_printer(writer, default_columns),
   77          cm: None,
   78          intr: token::get_ident_interner(),
   79          comments: None,
   80          literals: None,
   81          cur_cmnt_and_lit: CurrentCommentAndLiteral {
   82              cur_cmnt: 0,
   83              cur_lit: 0
   84          },
   85          boxes: RefCell::new(Vec::new()),
   86          ann: ann
   87      }
   88  }
   89  
   90  pub static indent_unit: uint = 4u;
   91  
   92  pub static default_columns: uint = 78u;
   93  
   94  // Requires you to pass an input filename and reader so that
   95  // it can scan the input text for comments and literals to
   96  // copy forward.
   97  pub fn print_crate<'a>(cm: &'a CodeMap,
   98                         span_diagnostic: &diagnostic::SpanHandler,
   99                         krate: &ast::Crate,
  100                         filename: ~str,
  101                         input: &mut io::Reader,
  102                         out: ~io::Writer,
  103                         ann: &'a PpAnn,
  104                         is_expanded: bool) -> IoResult<()> {
  105      let (cmnts, lits) = comments::gather_comments_and_literals(
  106          span_diagnostic,
  107          filename,
  108          input
  109      );
  110      let mut s = State {
  111          s: pp::mk_printer(out, default_columns),
  112          cm: Some(cm),
  113          intr: token::get_ident_interner(),
  114          comments: Some(cmnts),
  115          // If the code is post expansion, don't use the table of
  116          // literals, since it doesn't correspond with the literals
  117          // in the AST anymore.
  118          literals: if is_expanded {
  119              None
  120          } else {
  121              Some(lits)
  122          },
  123          cur_cmnt_and_lit: CurrentCommentAndLiteral {
  124              cur_cmnt: 0,
  125              cur_lit: 0
  126          },
  127          boxes: RefCell::new(Vec::new()),
  128          ann: ann
  129      };
  130      try!(s.print_mod(&krate.module, krate.attrs.as_slice()));
  131      try!(s.print_remaining_comments());
  132      eof(&mut s.s)
  133  }

  135  pub fn to_str(f: |&mut State| -> IoResult<()>) -> ~str {
  136      let mut s = rust_printer(~MemWriter::new());
  137      f(&mut s).unwrap();
  138      eof(&mut s.s).unwrap();
  139      unsafe {
  140          // FIXME(pcwalton): A nasty function to extract the string from an `io::Writer`
  141          // that we "know" to be a `MemWriter` that works around the lack of checked
  142          // downcasts.
  143          let (_, wr): (uint, ~MemWriter) = cast::transmute_copy(&s.s.out);
  144          let result = str::from_utf8_owned(wr.get_ref().to_owned()).unwrap();
  145          cast::forget(wr);
  146          result
  147      }
  148  }

  239  impl<'a> State<'a> {
  240      pub fn ibox(&mut self, u: uint) -> IoResult<()> {
  241          self.boxes.borrow_mut().push(pp::Inconsistent);
  242          pp::ibox(&mut self.s, u)
  243      }
  244  
  245      pub fn end(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> {
  246          self.boxes.borrow_mut().pop().unwrap();
  247          pp::end(&mut self.s)
  248      }
  249  
  250      pub fn cbox(&mut self, u: uint) -> IoResult<()> {
  251          self.boxes.borrow_mut().push(pp::Consistent);
  252          pp::cbox(&mut self.s, u)
  253      }
  254  
  255      // "raw box"
  256      pub fn rbox(&mut self, u: uint, b: pp::Breaks) -> IoResult<()> {
  257          self.boxes.borrow_mut().push(b);
  258          pp::rbox(&mut self.s, u, b)
  259      }
  260  
  261      pub fn nbsp(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> { word(&mut self.s, " ") }
  262  
  263      pub fn word_nbsp(&mut self, w: &str) -> IoResult<()> {
  264          try!(word(&mut self.s, w));
  265          self.nbsp()
  266      }
  267  
  268      pub fn word_space(&mut self, w: &str) -> IoResult<()> {
  269          try!(word(&mut self.s, w));
  270          space(&mut self.s)
  271      }
  272  
  273      pub fn popen(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> { word(&mut self.s, "(") }
  274  
  275      pub fn pclose(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> { word(&mut self.s, ")") }
  276  
  277      pub fn head(&mut self, w: &str) -> IoResult<()> {
  278          // outer-box is consistent
  279          try!(self.cbox(indent_unit));
  280          // head-box is inconsistent
  281          try!(self.ibox(w.len() + 1));
  282          // keyword that starts the head
  283          if !w.is_empty() {
  284              try!(self.word_nbsp(w));
  285          }
  286          Ok(())
  287      }
  288  
  289      pub fn bopen(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> {
  290          try!(word(&mut self.s, "{"));
  291          self.end() // close the head-box
  292      }
  293  
  294      pub fn bclose_(&mut self, span: codemap::Span,
  295                     indented: uint) -> IoResult<()> {
  296          self.bclose_maybe_open(span, indented, true)
  297      }
  298      pub fn bclose_maybe_open (&mut self, span: codemap::Span,
  299                                indented: uint, close_box: bool) -> IoResult<()> {
  300          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(span.hi));
  301          try!(self.break_offset_if_not_bol(1u, -(indented as int)));
  302          try!(word(&mut self.s, "}"));
  303          if close_box {
  304              try!(self.end()); // close the outer-box
  305          }
  306          Ok(())
  307      }
  308      pub fn bclose(&mut self, span: codemap::Span) -> IoResult<()> {
  309          self.bclose_(span, indent_unit)
  310      }
  311  
  312      pub fn is_begin(&mut self) -> bool {
  313          match self.s.last_token() { pp::Begin(_) => true, _ => false }
  314      }
  315  
  316      pub fn is_end(&mut self) -> bool {
  317          match self.s.last_token() { pp::End => true, _ => false }
  318      }
  319  
  320      pub fn is_bol(&mut self) -> bool {
  321          self.s.last_token().is_eof() || self.s.last_token().is_hardbreak_tok()
  322      }
  323  
  324      pub fn in_cbox(&mut self) -> bool {
  325          match self.boxes.borrow().last() {
  326              Some(&last_box) => last_box == pp::Consistent,
  327              None => false
  328          }
  329      }
  330  
  331      pub fn hardbreak_if_not_bol(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> {
  332          if !self.is_bol() {
  333              try!(hardbreak(&mut self.s))
  334          }
  335          Ok(())
  336      }
  337      pub fn space_if_not_bol(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> {
  338          if !self.is_bol() { try!(space(&mut self.s)); }
  339          Ok(())
  340      }
  341      pub fn break_offset_if_not_bol(&mut self, n: uint,
  342                                     off: int) -> IoResult<()> {
  343          if !self.is_bol() {
  344              break_offset(&mut self.s, n, off)
  345          } else {
  346              if off != 0 && self.s.last_token().is_hardbreak_tok() {
  347                  // We do something pretty sketchy here: tuck the nonzero
  348                  // offset-adjustment we were going to deposit along with the
  349                  // break into the previous hardbreak.
  350                  self.s.replace_last_token(pp::hardbreak_tok_offset(off));
  351              }
  352              Ok(())
  353          }
  354      }
  355  
  356      // Synthesizes a comment that was not textually present in the original source
  357      // file.
  358      pub fn synth_comment(&mut self, text: ~str) -> IoResult<()> {
  359          try!(word(&mut self.s, "/*"));
  360          try!(space(&mut self.s));
  361          try!(word(&mut self.s, text));
  362          try!(space(&mut self.s));
  363          word(&mut self.s, "*/")
  364      }
  365  
  366      pub fn commasep<T>(&mut self, b: Breaks, elts: &[T],
  367                         op: |&mut State, &T| -> IoResult<()>)
  368          -> IoResult<()> {
  369          try!(self.rbox(0u, b));
  370          let mut first = true;
  371          for elt in elts.iter() {
  372              if first { first = false; } else { try!(self.word_space(",")); }
  373              try!(op(self, elt));
  374          }
  375          self.end()
  376      }
  377  
  378  
  379      pub fn commasep_cmnt<T>(
  380                           &mut self,
  381                           b: Breaks,
  382                           elts: &[T],
  383                           op: |&mut State, &T| -> IoResult<()>,
  384                           get_span: |&T| -> codemap::Span) -> IoResult<()> {
  385          try!(self.rbox(0u, b));
  386          let len = elts.len();
  387          let mut i = 0u;
  388          for elt in elts.iter() {
  389              try!(self.maybe_print_comment(get_span(elt).hi));
  390              try!(op(self, elt));
  391              i += 1u;
  392              if i < len {
  393                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
  394                  try!(self.maybe_print_trailing_comment(get_span(elt),
  395                                                      Some(get_span(&elts[i]).hi)));
  396                  try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
  397              }
  398          }
  399          self.end()
  400      }
  401  
  402      pub fn commasep_exprs(&mut self, b: Breaks,
  403                            exprs: &[@ast::Expr]) -> IoResult<()> {
  404          self.commasep_cmnt(b, exprs, |s, &e| s.print_expr(e), |e| e.span)
  405      }

  407      pub fn print_mod(&mut self, _mod: &ast::Mod,
  408                       attrs: &[ast::Attribute]) -> IoResult<()> {
  409          try!(self.print_inner_attributes(attrs));
  410          for vitem in _mod.view_items.iter() {
  411              try!(self.print_view_item(vitem));
  412          }
  413          for item in _mod.items.iter() {
  414              try!(self.print_item(*item));
  415          }
  416          Ok(())
  417      }

  424          }

  431      pub fn print_opt_lifetime(&mut self,
  432                                lifetime: &Option<ast::Lifetime>) -> IoResult<()> {
  433          for l in lifetime.iter() {
  434              try!(self.print_lifetime(l));
  435              try!(self.nbsp());
  436          }
  437          Ok(())
  438      }
  439  
  440      pub fn print_type(&mut self, ty: &ast::Ty) -> IoResult<()> {
  441          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(ty.span.lo));
  442          try!(self.ibox(0u));
  443          match ty.node {
  444              ast::TyNil => try!(word(&mut self.s, "()")),
  445              ast::TyBot => try!(word(&mut self.s, "!")),
  446              ast::TyBox(ty) => {
  447                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "@"));
  448                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  449              }
  450              ast::TyUniq(ty) => {
  451                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "~"));
  452                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  453              }
  454              ast::TyVec(ty) => {
  455                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
  456                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  457                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
  458              }
  459              ast::TyPtr(ref mt) => {
  460                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "*"));
  461                  try!(self.print_mt(mt));
  462              }
  463              ast::TyRptr(ref lifetime, ref mt) => {
  464                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "&"));
  465                  try!(self.print_opt_lifetime(lifetime));
  466                  try!(self.print_mt(mt));
  467              }
  468              ast::TyTup(ref elts) => {
  469                  try!(self.popen());
  470                  try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent, elts.as_slice(),
  471                                     |s, ty| s.print_type_ref(ty)));
  472                  if elts.len() == 1 {
  473                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
  474                  }
  475                  try!(self.pclose());
  476              }
  477              ast::TyBareFn(f) => {
  478                  let generics = ast::Generics {
  479                      lifetimes: f.lifetimes.clone(),
  480                      ty_params: OwnedSlice::empty()
  481                  };
  482                  try!(self.print_ty_fn(Some(f.abis), None, &None,
  483                                     f.purity, ast::Many, f.decl, None, &None,
  484                                     Some(&generics), None));
  485              }
  486              ast::TyClosure(f) => {
  487                  let generics = ast::Generics {
  488                      lifetimes: f.lifetimes.clone(),
  489                      ty_params: OwnedSlice::empty()
  490                  };
  491                  try!(self.print_ty_fn(None, Some(f.sigil), &f.region,
  492                                     f.purity, f.onceness, f.decl, None, &f.bounds,
  493                                     Some(&generics), None));
  494              }
  495              ast::TyPath(ref path, ref bounds, _) => {
  496                  try!(self.print_bounded_path(path, bounds));
  497              }
  498              ast::TyFixedLengthVec(ty, v) => {
  499                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
  500                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  501                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ", .."));
  502                  try!(self.print_expr(v));
  503                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
  504              }
  505              ast::TyTypeof(e) => {
  506                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "typeof("));
  507                  try!(self.print_expr(e));
  508                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ")"));
  509              }
  510              ast::TyInfer => {
  511                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "_"));
  512              }
  513          }
  514          self.end()
  515      }
  516  
  517      pub fn print_type_ref(&mut self, ty: &P<ast::Ty>) -> IoResult<()> {
  518          self.print_type(*ty)
  519      }

  521      pub fn print_foreign_item(&mut self,
  522                                item: &ast::ForeignItem) -> IoResult<()> {
  523          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  524          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(item.span.lo));
  525          try!(self.print_outer_attributes(item.attrs.as_slice()));
  526          match item.node {
  527              ast::ForeignItemFn(decl, ref generics) => {
  528                  try!(self.print_fn(decl, None, AbiSet::Rust(), item.ident, generics,
  529                  None, item.vis));
  530                  try!(self.end()); // end head-ibox
  531                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  532                  self.end() // end the outer fn box
  533              }
  534              ast::ForeignItemStatic(t, m) => {
  535                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "static")));
  536                  if m {
  537                      try!(self.word_space("mut"));
  538                  }
  539                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  540                  try!(self.word_space(":"));
  541                  try!(self.print_type(t));
  542                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  543                  try!(self.end()); // end the head-ibox
  544                  self.end() // end the outer cbox
  545              }
  546          }
  547      }
  548  
  549      pub fn print_item(&mut self, item: &ast::Item) -> IoResult<()> {
  550          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  551          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(item.span.lo));
  552          try!(self.print_outer_attributes(item.attrs.as_slice()));
  553          try!(self.ann.pre(self, NodeItem(item)));
  554          match item.node {
  555              ast::ItemStatic(ty, m, expr) => {
  556                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "static")));
  557                  if m == ast::MutMutable {
  558                      try!(self.word_space("mut"));
  559                  }
  560                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  561                  try!(self.word_space(":"));
  562                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  563                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
  564                  try!(self.end()); // end the head-ibox
  565  
  566                  try!(self.word_space("="));
  567                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
  568                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  569                  try!(self.end()); // end the outer cbox
  570              }
  571              ast::ItemFn(decl, purity, abi, ref typarams, body) => {
  572                  try!(self.print_fn(
  573                      decl,
  574                      Some(purity),
  575                      abi,
  576                      item.ident,
  577                      typarams,
  578                      None,
  579                      item.vis
  580                  ));
  581                  try!(word(&mut self.s, " "));
  582                  try!(self.print_block_with_attrs(body, item.attrs.as_slice()));
  583              }
  584              ast::ItemMod(ref _mod) => {
  585                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "mod")));
  586                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  587                  try!(self.nbsp());
  588                  try!(self.bopen());
  589                  try!(self.print_mod(_mod, item.attrs.as_slice()));
  590                  try!(self.bclose(item.span));
  591              }
  592              ast::ItemForeignMod(ref nmod) => {
  593                  try!(self.head("extern"));
  594                  try!(self.word_nbsp(nmod.abis.to_str()));
  595                  try!(self.bopen());
  596                  try!(self.print_foreign_mod(nmod, item.attrs.as_slice()));
  597                  try!(self.bclose(item.span));
  598              }
  599              ast::ItemTy(ty, ref params) => {
  600                  try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
  601                  try!(self.ibox(0u));
  602                  try!(self.word_nbsp(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "type")));
  603                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  604                  try!(self.print_generics(params));
  605                  try!(self.end()); // end the inner ibox
  606  
  607                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
  608                  try!(self.word_space("="));
  609                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  610                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  611                  try!(self.end()); // end the outer ibox
  612              }
  613              ast::ItemEnum(ref enum_definition, ref params) => {
  614                  try!(self.print_enum_def(
  615                      enum_definition,
  616                      params,
  617                      item.ident,
  618                      item.span,
  619                      item.vis
  620                  ));
  621              }
  622              ast::ItemStruct(struct_def, ref generics) => {
  623                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "struct")));
  624                  try!(self.print_struct(struct_def, generics, item.ident, item.span));
  625              }
  626  
  627              ast::ItemImpl(ref generics, ref opt_trait, ty, ref methods) => {
  628                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "impl")));
  629                  if generics.is_parameterized() {
  630                      try!(self.print_generics(generics));
  631                      try!(space(&mut self.s));
  632                  }
  633  
  634                  match opt_trait {
  635                      &Some(ref t) => {
  636                          try!(self.print_trait_ref(t));
  637                          try!(space(&mut self.s));
  638                          try!(self.word_space("for"));
  639                      }
  640                      &None => {}
  641                  }
  642  
  643                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  644  
  645                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
  646                  try!(self.bopen());
  647                  try!(self.print_inner_attributes(item.attrs.as_slice()));
  648                  for meth in methods.iter() {
  649                      try!(self.print_method(*meth));
  650                  }
  651                  try!(self.bclose(item.span));
  652              }
  653              ast::ItemTrait(ref generics, ref traits, ref methods) => {
  654                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "trait")));
  655                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  656                  try!(self.print_generics(generics));
  657                  if traits.len() != 0u {
  658                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ":"));
  659                      for (i, trait_) in traits.iter().enumerate() {
  660                          try!(self.nbsp());
  661                          if i != 0 {
  662                              try!(self.word_space("+"));
  663                          }
  664                          try!(self.print_path(&trait_.path, false));
  665                      }
  666                  }
  667                  try!(word(&mut self.s, " "));
  668                  try!(self.bopen());
  669                  for meth in methods.iter() {
  670                      try!(self.print_trait_method(meth));
  671                  }
  672                  try!(self.bclose(item.span));
  673              }
  674              // I think it's reasonable to hide the context here:
  675              ast::ItemMac(codemap::Spanned { node: ast::MacInvocTT(ref pth, ref tts, _),
  676                                              ..}) => {
  677                  try!(self.print_visibility(item.vis));
  678                  try!(self.print_path(pth, false));
  679                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "! "));
  680                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  681                  try!(self.cbox(indent_unit));
  682                  try!(self.popen());
  683                  try!(self.print_tts(&(tts.as_slice())));
  684                  try!(self.pclose());
  685                  try!(self.end());
  686              }
  687          }
  688          self.ann.post(self, NodeItem(item))
  689      }
  690  
  691      fn print_trait_ref(&mut self, t: &ast::TraitRef) -> IoResult<()> {
  692          self.print_path(&t.path, false)
  693      }

  695      pub fn print_enum_def(&mut self, enum_definition: &ast::EnumDef,
  696                            generics: &ast::Generics, ident: ast::Ident,
  697                            span: codemap::Span,
  698                            visibility: ast::Visibility) -> IoResult<()> {
  699          try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(visibility, "enum")));
  700          try!(self.print_ident(ident));
  701          try!(self.print_generics(generics));
  702          try!(space(&mut self.s));
  703          self.print_variants(enum_definition.variants.as_slice(), span)
  704      }

  706      pub fn print_variants(&mut self,
  707                            variants: &[P<ast::Variant>],
  708                            span: codemap::Span) -> IoResult<()> {
  709          try!(self.bopen());
  710          for &v in variants.iter() {
  711              try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
  712              try!(self.maybe_print_comment(v.span.lo));
  713              try!(self.print_outer_attributes(v.node.attrs.as_slice()));
  714              try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
  715              try!(self.print_variant(v));
  716              try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
  717              try!(self.end());
  718              try!(self.maybe_print_trailing_comment(v.span, None));
  719          }
  720          self.bclose(span)
  721      }

  723      pub fn print_visibility(&mut self, vis: ast::Visibility) -> IoResult<()> {
  724          match vis {
  725              ast::Private => self.word_nbsp("priv"),
  726              ast::Public => self.word_nbsp("pub"),
  727              ast::Inherited => Ok(())
  728          }
  729      }
  730  
  731      pub fn print_struct(&mut self,
  732                          struct_def: &ast::StructDef,
  733                          generics: &ast::Generics,
  734                          ident: ast::Ident,
  735                          span: codemap::Span) -> IoResult<()> {
  736          try!(self.print_ident(ident));
  737          try!(self.print_generics(generics));
  738          if ast_util::struct_def_is_tuple_like(struct_def) {
  739              if !struct_def.fields.is_empty() {
  740                  try!(self.popen());
  741                  try!(self.commasep(
  742                      Inconsistent, struct_def.fields.as_slice(),
  743                      |s, field| {
  744                          match field.node.kind {
  745                              ast::NamedField(..) => fail!("unexpected named field"),
  746                              ast::UnnamedField => {
  747                                  try!(s.maybe_print_comment(field.span.lo));
  748                                  s.print_type(field.node.ty)
  749                              }
  750                          }
  751                      }
  752                  ));
  753                  try!(self.pclose());
  754              }
  755              try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  756              try!(self.end());
  757              self.end() // close the outer-box
  758          } else {
  759              try!(self.nbsp());
  760              try!(self.bopen());
  761              try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  762  
  763              for field in struct_def.fields.iter() {
  764                  match field.node.kind {
  765                      ast::UnnamedField => fail!("unexpected unnamed field"),
  766                      ast::NamedField(ident, visibility) => {
  767                          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  768                          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(field.span.lo));
  769                          try!(self.print_outer_attributes(field.node.attrs.as_slice()));
  770                          try!(self.print_visibility(visibility));
  771                          try!(self.print_ident(ident));
  772                          try!(self.word_nbsp(":"));
  773                          try!(self.print_type(field.node.ty));
  774                          try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
  775                      }
  776                  }
  777              }
  778  
  779              self.bclose(span)
  780          }
  781      }
  782  
  783      /// This doesn't deserve to be called "pretty" printing, but it should be
  784      /// meaning-preserving. A quick hack that might help would be to look at the
  785      /// spans embedded in the TTs to decide where to put spaces and newlines.
  786      /// But it'd be better to parse these according to the grammar of the
  787      /// appropriate macro, transcribe back into the grammar we just parsed from,
  788      /// and then pretty-print the resulting AST nodes (so, e.g., we print
  789      /// expression arguments as expressions). It can be done! I think.
  790      pub fn print_tt(&mut self, tt: &ast::TokenTree) -> IoResult<()> {
  791          match *tt {
  792              ast::TTDelim(ref tts) => self.print_tts(&(tts.as_slice())),
  793              ast::TTTok(_, ref tk) => {
  794                  word(&mut self.s, parse::token::to_str(tk))
  795              }
  796              ast::TTSeq(_, ref tts, ref sep, zerok) => {
  797                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "$("));
  798                  for tt_elt in (*tts).iter() {
  799                      try!(self.print_tt(tt_elt));
  800                  }
  801                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ")"));
  802                  match *sep {
  803                      Some(ref tk) => {
  804                          try!(word(&mut self.s, parse::token::to_str(tk)));
  805                      }
  806                      None => ()
  807                  }
  808                  word(&mut self.s, if zerok { "*" } else { "+" })
  809              }
  810              ast::TTNonterminal(_, name) => {
  811                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "$"));
  812                  self.print_ident(name)
  813              }
  814          }
  815      }
  816  
  817      pub fn print_tts(&mut self, tts: & &[ast::TokenTree]) -> IoResult<()> {
  818          try!(self.ibox(0));
  819          for (i, tt) in tts.iter().enumerate() {
  820              if i != 0 {
  821                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
  822              }
  823              try!(self.print_tt(tt));
  824          }
  825          self.end()
  826      }
  827  
  828      pub fn print_variant(&mut self, v: &ast::Variant) -> IoResult<()> {
  829          try!(self.print_visibility(v.node.vis));
  830          match v.node.kind {
  831              ast::TupleVariantKind(ref args) => {
  832                  try!(self.print_ident(v.node.name));
  833                  if !args.is_empty() {
  834                      try!(self.popen());
  835                      try!(self.commasep(Consistent,
  836                                         args.as_slice(),
  837                                         |s, arg| s.print_type(arg.ty)));
  838                      try!(self.pclose());
  839                  }
  840              }
  841              ast::StructVariantKind(struct_def) => {
  842                  try!(self.head(""));
  843                  let generics = ast_util::empty_generics();
  844                  try!(self.print_struct(struct_def, &generics, v.node.name, v.span));
  845              }
  846          }
  847          match v.node.disr_expr {
  848              Some(d) => {
  849                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
  850                  try!(self.word_space("="));
  851                  self.print_expr(d)
  852              }
  853              _ => Ok(())
  854          }
  855      }
  856  
  857      pub fn print_ty_method(&mut self, m: &ast::TypeMethod) -> IoResult<()> {
  858          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  859          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(m.span.lo));
  860          try!(self.print_outer_attributes(m.attrs.as_slice()));
  861          try!(self.print_ty_fn(None,
  862                                None,
  863                                &None,
  864                                m.purity,
  865                                ast::Many,
  866                                m.decl,
  867                                Some(m.ident),
  868                                &None,
  869                                Some(&m.generics),
  870                                Some(m.explicit_self.node)));
  871          word(&mut self.s, ";")
  872      }
  873  
  874      pub fn print_trait_method(&mut self,
  875                                m: &ast::TraitMethod) -> IoResult<()> {
  876          match *m {
  877              Required(ref ty_m) => self.print_ty_method(ty_m),
  878              Provided(m) => self.print_method(m)
  879          }
  880      }
  881  
  882      pub fn print_method(&mut self, meth: &ast::Method) -> IoResult<()> {
  883          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  884          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(meth.span.lo));
  885          try!(self.print_outer_attributes(meth.attrs.as_slice()));
  886          try!(self.print_fn(meth.decl, Some(meth.purity), AbiSet::Rust(),
  887                          meth.ident, &meth.generics, Some(meth.explicit_self.node),
  888                          meth.vis));
  889          try!(word(&mut self.s, " "));
  890          self.print_block_with_attrs(meth.body, meth.attrs.as_slice())
  891      }
  892  
  893      pub fn print_outer_attributes(&mut self,
  894                                    attrs: &[ast::Attribute]) -> IoResult<()> {
  895          let mut count = 0;
  896          for attr in attrs.iter() {
  897              match attr.node.style {
  898                  ast::AttrOuter => {
  899                      try!(self.print_attribute(attr));
  900                      count += 1;
  901                  }
  902                  _ => {/* fallthrough */ }
  903              }
  904          }
  905          if count > 0 {
  906              try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  907          }
  908          Ok(())
  909      }
  910  
  911      pub fn print_inner_attributes(&mut self,
  912                                    attrs: &[ast::Attribute]) -> IoResult<()> {
  913          let mut count = 0;
  914          for attr in attrs.iter() {
  915              match attr.node.style {
  916                  ast::AttrInner => {
  917                      try!(self.print_attribute(attr));
  918                      if !attr.node.is_sugared_doc {
  919                          try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  920                      }
  921                      count += 1;
  922                  }
  923                  _ => {/* fallthrough */ }
  924              }
  925          }
  926          if count > 0 {
  927              try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  928          }
  929          Ok(())
  930      }
  931  
  932      pub fn print_attribute(&mut self, attr: &ast::Attribute) -> IoResult<()> {
  933          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  934          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(attr.span.lo));
  935          if attr.node.is_sugared_doc {
  936              word(&mut self.s, attr.value_str().unwrap().get())
  937          } else {
  938              try!(word(&mut self.s, "#["));
  939              try!(self.print_meta_item(attr.meta()));
  940              word(&mut self.s, "]")
  941          }
  942      }
  943  
  944  
  945      pub fn print_stmt(&mut self, st: &ast::Stmt) -> IoResult<()> {
  946          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(st.span.lo));
  947          match st.node {
  948              ast::StmtDecl(decl, _) => {
  949                  try!(self.print_decl(decl));
  950              }
  951              ast::StmtExpr(expr, _) => {
  952                  try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
  953                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
  954              }
  955              ast::StmtSemi(expr, _) => {
  956                  try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
  957                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
  958                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  959              }
  960              ast::StmtMac(ref mac, semi) => {
  961                  try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
  962                  try!(self.print_mac(mac));
  963                  if semi {
  964                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  965                  }
  966              }
  967          }
  968          if parse::classify::stmt_ends_with_semi(st) {
  969              try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  970          }
  971          self.maybe_print_trailing_comment(st.span, None)
  972      }

  974      pub fn print_block(&mut self, blk: &ast::Block) -> IoResult<()> {
  975          self.print_block_with_attrs(blk, &[])
  976      }
  977  
  978      pub fn print_block_unclosed(&mut self, blk: &ast::Block) -> IoResult<()> {
  979          self.print_block_unclosed_indent(blk, indent_unit)
  980      }
  981  
  982      pub fn print_block_unclosed_indent(&mut self, blk: &ast::Block,
  983                                         indented: uint) -> IoResult<()> {
  984          self.print_block_maybe_unclosed(blk, indented, &[], false)
  985      }
  986  
  987      pub fn print_block_with_attrs(&mut self,
  988                                    blk: &ast::Block,
  989                                    attrs: &[ast::Attribute]) -> IoResult<()> {
  990          self.print_block_maybe_unclosed(blk, indent_unit, attrs, true)
  991      }
  992  
  993      pub fn print_block_maybe_unclosed(&mut self,
  994                                        blk: &ast::Block,
  995                                        indented: uint,
  996                                        attrs: &[ast::Attribute],
  997                                        close_box: bool) -> IoResult<()> {
  998          match blk.rules {
  999              ast::UnsafeBlock(..) => try!(self.word_space("unsafe")),
 1000              ast::DefaultBlock => ()
 1001          }
 1002          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(blk.span.lo));
 1003          try!(self.ann.pre(self, NodeBlock(blk)));
 1004          try!(self.bopen());
 1005  
 1006          try!(self.print_inner_attributes(attrs));
 1007  
 1008          for vi in blk.view_items.iter() {
 1009              try!(self.print_view_item(vi));
 1010          }
 1011          for st in blk.stmts.iter() {
 1012              try!(self.print_stmt(*st));
 1013          }
 1014          match blk.expr {
 1015              Some(expr) => {
 1016                  try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
 1017                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1018                  try!(self.maybe_print_trailing_comment(expr.span, Some(blk.span.hi)));
 1019              }
 1020              _ => ()
 1021          }
 1022          try!(self.bclose_maybe_open(blk.span, indented, close_box));
 1023          self.ann.post(self, NodeBlock(blk))
 1024      }
 1025  
 1026      fn print_else(&mut self, els: Option<@ast::Expr>) -> IoResult<()> {
 1027          match els {
 1028              Some(_else) => {
 1029                  match _else.node {
 1030                      // "another else-if"
 1031                      ast::ExprIf(i, t, e) => {
 1032                          try!(self.cbox(indent_unit - 1u));
 1033                          try!(self.ibox(0u));
 1034                          try!(word(&mut self.s, " else if "));
 1035                          try!(self.print_expr(i));
 1036                          try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1037                          try!(self.print_block(t));
 1038                          self.print_else(e)
 1039                      }
 1040                      // "final else"
 1041                      ast::ExprBlock(b) => {
 1042                          try!(self.cbox(indent_unit - 1u));
 1043                          try!(self.ibox(0u));
 1044                          try!(word(&mut self.s, " else "));
 1045                          self.print_block(b)
 1046                      }
 1047                      // BLEAH, constraints would be great here
 1048                      _ => {
 1049                          fail!("print_if saw if with weird alternative");
 1050                      }
 1051                  }
 1052              }
 1053              _ => Ok(())
 1054          }
 1055      }
 1056  
 1057      pub fn print_if(&mut self, test: &ast::Expr, blk: &ast::Block,
 1058                      elseopt: Option<@ast::Expr>, chk: bool) -> IoResult<()> {
 1059          try!(self.head("if"));
 1060          if chk { try!(self.word_nbsp("check")); }
 1061          try!(self.print_expr(test));
 1062          try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1063          try!(self.print_block(blk));
 1064          self.print_else(elseopt)
 1065      }

 1067      pub fn print_mac(&mut self, m: &ast::Mac) -> IoResult<()> {
 1068          match m.node {
 1069              // I think it's reasonable to hide the ctxt here:
 1070              ast::MacInvocTT(ref pth, ref tts, _) => {
 1071                  try!(self.print_path(pth, false));
 1072                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "!"));
 1073                  try!(self.popen());
 1074                  try!(self.print_tts(&tts.as_slice()));
 1075                  self.pclose()
 1076              }
 1077          }
 1078      }

 1080      pub fn print_expr_vstore(&mut self, t: ast::ExprVstore) -> IoResult<()> {
 1081          match t {
 1082              ast::ExprVstoreUniq => word(&mut self.s, "~"),
 1083              ast::ExprVstoreSlice => word(&mut self.s, "&"),
 1084              ast::ExprVstoreMutSlice => {
 1085                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "&"));
 1086                  word(&mut self.s, "mut")
 1087              }
 1088          }
 1089      }

 1091      fn print_call_post(&mut self, args: &[@ast::Expr]) -> IoResult<()> {
 1092          try!(self.popen());
 1093          try!(self.commasep_exprs(Inconsistent, args));
 1094          self.pclose()
 1095      }

 1097      pub fn print_expr(&mut self, expr: &ast::Expr) -> IoResult<()> {
 1098          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(expr.span.lo));
 1099          try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
 1100          try!(self.ann.pre(self, NodeExpr(expr)));
 1101          match expr.node {
 1102              ast::ExprVstore(e, v) => {
 1103                  try!(self.print_expr_vstore(v));
 1104                  try!(self.print_expr(e));
 1105              },
 1106              ast::ExprBox(p, e) => {
 1107                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "box"));
 1108                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "("));
 1109                  try!(self.print_expr(p));
 1110                  try!(self.word_space(")"));
 1111                  try!(self.print_expr(e));
 1112              }
 1113              ast::ExprVec(ref exprs, mutbl) => {
 1114                  try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
 1115                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
 1116                  if mutbl == ast::MutMutable {
 1117                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "mut"));
 1118                      if exprs.len() > 0u { try!(self.nbsp()); }
 1119                  }
 1120                  try!(self.commasep_exprs(Inconsistent, exprs.as_slice()));
 1121                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
 1122                  try!(self.end());
 1123              }
 1124  
 1125              ast::ExprRepeat(element, count, mutbl) => {
 1126                  try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
 1127                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
 1128                  if mutbl == ast::MutMutable {
 1129                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "mut"));
 1130                      try!(self.nbsp());
 1131                  }
 1132                  try!(self.print_expr(element));
 1133                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
 1134                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ".."));
 1135                  try!(self.print_expr(count));
 1136                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
 1137                  try!(self.end());
 1138              }
 1139  
 1140              ast::ExprStruct(ref path, ref fields, wth) => {
 1141                  try!(self.print_path(path, true));
 1142                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "{"));
 1143                  try!(self.commasep_cmnt(
 1144                      Consistent,
 1145                      fields.as_slice(),
 1146                      |s, field| {
 1147                          try!(s.ibox(indent_unit));
 1148                          try!(s.print_ident(field.ident.node));
 1149                          try!(s.word_space(":"));
 1150                          try!(s.print_expr(field.expr));
 1151                          s.end()
 1152                      },
 1153                      |f| f.span));
 1154                  match wth {
 1155                      Some(expr) => {
 1156                          try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
 1157                          if !fields.is_empty() {
 1158                              try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
 1159                              try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1160                          }
 1161                          try!(word(&mut self.s, ".."));
 1162                          try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1163                          try!(self.end());
 1164                      }
 1165                      _ => try!(word(&mut self.s, ","))
 1166                  }
 1167                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "}"));
 1168              }
 1169              ast::ExprTup(ref exprs) => {
 1170                  try!(self.popen());
 1171                  try!(self.commasep_exprs(Inconsistent, exprs.as_slice()));
 1172                  if exprs.len() == 1 {
 1173                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
 1174                  }
 1175                  try!(self.pclose());
 1176              }
 1177              ast::ExprCall(func, ref args) => {
 1178                  try!(self.print_expr(func));
 1179                  try!(self.print_call_post(args.as_slice()));
 1180              }
 1181              ast::ExprMethodCall(ident, ref tys, ref args) => {
 1182                  let base_args = args.slice_from(1);
 1183                  try!(self.print_expr(*args.get(0)));
 1184                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "."));
 1185                  try!(self.print_ident(ident));
 1186                  if tys.len() > 0u {
 1187                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "::<"));
 1188                      try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent, tys.as_slice(),
 1189                                         |s, ty| s.print_type_ref(ty)));
 1190                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ">"));
 1191                  }
 1192                  try!(self.print_call_post(base_args));
 1193              }
 1194              ast::ExprBinary(op, lhs, rhs) => {
 1195                  try!(self.print_expr(lhs));
 1196                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1197                  try!(self.word_space(ast_util::binop_to_str(op)));
 1198                  try!(self.print_expr(rhs));
 1199              }
 1200              ast::ExprUnary(op, expr) => {
 1201                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ast_util::unop_to_str(op)));
 1202                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1203              }
 1204              ast::ExprAddrOf(m, expr) => {
 1205                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "&"));
 1206                  try!(self.print_mutability(m));
 1207                  // Avoid `& &e` => `&&e`.
 1208                  match (m, &expr.node) {
 1209                      (ast::MutImmutable, &ast::ExprAddrOf(..)) => try!(space(&mut self.s)),
 1210                      _ => { }
 1211                  }
 1212                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1213              }
 1214              ast::ExprLit(lit) => try!(self.print_literal(lit)),
 1215              ast::ExprCast(expr, ty) => {
 1216                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1217                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1218                  try!(self.word_space("as"));
 1219                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
 1220              }
 1221              ast::ExprIf(test, blk, elseopt) => {
 1222                  try!(self.print_if(test, blk, elseopt, false));
 1223              }
 1224              ast::ExprWhile(test, blk) => {
 1225                  try!(self.head("while"));
 1226                  try!(self.print_expr(test));
 1227                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1228                  try!(self.print_block(blk));
 1229              }
 1230              ast::ExprForLoop(pat, iter, blk, opt_ident) => {
 1231                  for ident in opt_ident.iter() {
 1232                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "'"));
 1233                      try!(self.print_ident(*ident));
 1234                      try!(self.word_space(":"));
 1235                  }
 1236                  try!(self.head("for"));
 1237                  try!(self.print_pat(pat));
 1238                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1239                  try!(self.word_space("in"));
 1240                  try!(self.print_expr(iter));
 1241                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1242                  try!(self.print_block(blk));
 1243              }
 1244              ast::ExprLoop(blk, opt_ident) => {
 1245                  for ident in opt_ident.iter() {
 1246                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "'"));
 1247                      try!(self.print_ident(*ident));
 1248                      try!(self.word_space(":"));
 1249                  }
 1250                  try!(self.head("loop"));
 1251                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1252                  try!(self.print_block(blk));
 1253              }
 1254              ast::ExprMatch(expr, ref arms) => {
 1255                  try!(self.cbox(indent_unit));
 1256                  try!(self.ibox(4));
 1257                  try!(self.word_nbsp("match"));
 1258                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1259                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1260                  try!(self.bopen());
 1261                  let len = arms.len();
 1262                  for (i, arm) in arms.iter().enumerate() {
 1263                      try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1264                      try!(self.cbox(indent_unit));
 1265                      try!(self.ibox(0u));
 1266                      let mut first = true;
 1267                      for p in arm.pats.iter() {
 1268                          if first {
 1269                              first = false;
 1270                          } else {
 1271                              try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1272                              try!(self.word_space("|"));
 1273                          }
 1274                          try!(self.print_pat(*p));
 1275                      }
 1276                      try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1277                      match arm.guard {
 1278                          Some(e) => {
 1279                              try!(self.word_space("if"));
 1280                              try!(self.print_expr(e));
 1281                              try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1282                          }
 1283                          None => ()
 1284                      }
 1285                      try!(self.word_space("=>"));
 1286  
 1287                      match arm.body.node {
 1288                          ast::ExprBlock(blk) => {
 1289                              // the block will close the pattern's ibox
 1290                              try!(self.print_block_unclosed_indent(blk, indent_unit));
 1291                          }
 1292                          _ => {
 1293                              try!(self.end()); // close the ibox for the pattern
 1294                              try!(self.print_expr(arm.body));
 1295                          }
 1296                      }
 1297                      if !expr_is_simple_block(expr)
 1298                          && i < len - 1 {
 1299                          try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
 1300                      }
 1301                      try!(self.end()); // close enclosing cbox
 1302                  }
 1303                  try!(self.bclose_(expr.span, indent_unit));
 1304              }
 1305              ast::ExprFnBlock(decl, body) => {
 1306                  // in do/for blocks we don't want to show an empty
 1307                  // argument list, but at this point we don't know which
 1308                  // we are inside.
 1309                  //
 1310                  // if !decl.inputs.is_empty() {
 1311                  try!(self.print_fn_block_args(decl));
 1312                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1313                  // }
 1314                  assert!(body.stmts.is_empty());
 1315                  assert!(body.expr.is_some());
 1316                  // we extract the block, so as not to create another set of boxes
 1317                  match body.expr.unwrap().node {
 1318                      ast::ExprBlock(blk) => {
 1319                          try!(self.print_block_unclosed(blk));
 1320                      }
 1321                      _ => {
 1322                          // this is a bare expression
 1323                          try!(self.print_expr(body.expr.unwrap()));
 1324                          try!(self.end()); // need to close a box
 1325                      }
 1326                  }
 1327                  // a box will be closed by print_expr, but we didn't want an overall
 1328                  // wrapper so we closed the corresponding opening. so create an
 1329                  // empty box to satisfy the close.
 1330                  try!(self.ibox(0));
 1331              }
 1332              ast::ExprProc(decl, body) => {
 1333                  // in do/for blocks we don't want to show an empty
 1334                  // argument list, but at this point we don't know which
 1335                  // we are inside.
 1336                  //
 1337                  // if !decl.inputs.is_empty() {
 1338                  try!(self.print_proc_args(decl));
 1339                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1340                  // }
 1341                  assert!(body.stmts.is_empty());
 1342                  assert!(body.expr.is_some());
 1343                  // we extract the block, so as not to create another set of boxes
 1344                  match body.expr.unwrap().node {
 1345                      ast::ExprBlock(blk) => {
 1346                          try!(self.print_block_unclosed(blk));
 1347                      }
 1348                      _ => {
 1349                          // this is a bare expression
 1350                          try!(self.print_expr(body.expr.unwrap()));
 1351                          try!(self.end()); // need to close a box
 1352                      }
 1353                  }
 1354                  // a box will be closed by print_expr, but we didn't want an overall
 1355                  // wrapper so we closed the corresponding opening. so create an
 1356                  // empty box to satisfy the close.
 1357                  try!(self.ibox(0));
 1358              }
 1359              ast::ExprBlock(blk) => {
 1360                  // containing cbox, will be closed by print-block at }
 1361                  try!(self.cbox(indent_unit));
 1362                  // head-box, will be closed by print-block after {
 1363                  try!(self.ibox(0u));
 1364                  try!(self.print_block(blk));
 1365              }
 1366              ast::ExprAssign(lhs, rhs) => {
 1367                  try!(self.print_expr(lhs));
 1368                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1369                  try!(self.word_space("="));
 1370                  try!(self.print_expr(rhs));
 1371              }
 1372              ast::ExprAssignOp(op, lhs, rhs) => {
 1373                  try!(self.print_expr(lhs));
 1374                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1375                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ast_util::binop_to_str(op)));
 1376                  try!(self.word_space("="));
 1377                  try!(self.print_expr(rhs));
 1378              }
 1379              ast::ExprField(expr, id, ref tys) => {
 1380                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1381                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "."));
 1382                  try!(self.print_ident(id));
 1383                  if tys.len() > 0u {
 1384                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "::<"));
 1385                      try!(self.commasep(
 1386                          Inconsistent, tys.as_slice(),
 1387                          |s, ty| s.print_type_ref(ty)));
 1388                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ">"));
 1389                  }
 1390              }
 1391              ast::ExprIndex(expr, index) => {
 1392                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1393                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
 1394                  try!(self.print_expr(index));
 1395                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
 1396              }
 1397              ast::ExprPath(ref path) => try!(self.print_path(path, true)),
 1398              ast::ExprBreak(opt_ident) => {
 1399                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "break"));
 1400                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1401                  for ident in opt_ident.iter() {
 1402                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "'"));
 1403                      try!(self.print_ident(*ident));
 1404                      try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1405                  }
 1406              }
 1407              ast::ExprAgain(opt_ident) => {
 1408                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "continue"));
 1409                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1410                  for ident in opt_ident.iter() {
 1411                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "'"));
 1412                      try!(self.print_ident(*ident));
 1413                      try!(space(&mut self.s))
 1414                  }
 1415              }
 1416              ast::ExprRet(result) => {
 1417                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "return"));
 1418                  match result {
 1419                      Some(expr) => {
 1420                          try!(word(&mut self.s, " "));
 1421                          try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1422                      }
 1423                      _ => ()
 1424                  }
 1425              }
 1426              ast::ExprInlineAsm(ref a) => {
 1427                  if a.volatile {
 1428                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "__volatile__ asm!"));
 1429                  } else {
 1430                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "asm!"));
 1431                  }
 1432                  try!(self.popen());
 1433                  try!(self.print_string(a.asm.get(), a.asm_str_style));
 1434                  try!(self.word_space(":"));
 1435                  for &(ref co, o) in a.outputs.iter() {
 1436                      try!(self.print_string(co.get(), ast::CookedStr));
 1437                      try!(self.popen());
 1438                      try!(self.print_expr(o));
 1439                      try!(self.pclose());
 1440                      try!(self.word_space(","));
 1441                  }
 1442                  try!(self.word_space(":"));
 1443                  for &(ref co, o) in a.inputs.iter() {
 1444                      try!(self.print_string(co.get(), ast::CookedStr));
 1445                      try!(self.popen());
 1446                      try!(self.print_expr(o));
 1447                      try!(self.pclose());
 1448                      try!(self.word_space(","));
 1449                  }
 1450                  try!(self.word_space(":"));
 1451                  try!(self.print_string(a.clobbers.get(), ast::CookedStr));
 1452                  try!(self.pclose());
 1453              }
 1454              ast::ExprMac(ref m) => try!(self.print_mac(m)),
 1455              ast::ExprParen(e) => {
 1456                  try!(self.popen());
 1457                  try!(self.print_expr(e));
 1458                  try!(self.pclose());
 1459              }
 1460          }
 1461          try!(self.ann.post(self, NodeExpr(expr)));
 1462          self.end()
 1463      }

 1517      fn print_path_(&mut self,
 1518                     path: &ast::Path,
 1519                     colons_before_params: bool,
 1520                     opt_bounds: &Option<OwnedSlice<ast::TyParamBound>>)
 1521          -> IoResult<()> {
 1522          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(path.span.lo));
 1523          if path.global {
 1524              try!(word(&mut self.s, "::"));
 1525          }
 1526  
 1527          let mut first = true;
 1528          for (i, segment) in path.segments.iter().enumerate() {
 1529              if first {
 1530                  first = false
 1531              } else {
 1532                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "::"))
 1533              }
 1534  
 1535              try!(self.print_ident(segment.identifier));
 1536  
 1537              // If this is the last segment, print the bounds.
 1538              if i == path.segments.len() - 1 {
 1539                  match *opt_bounds {
 1540                      None => {}
 1541                      Some(ref bounds) => try!(self.print_bounds(bounds, true)),
 1542                  }
 1543              }
 1544  
 1545              if !segment.lifetimes.is_empty() || !segment.types.is_empty() {
 1546                  if colons_before_params {
 1547                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "::"))
 1548                  }
 1549                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "<"));
 1550  
 1551                  let mut comma = false;
 1552                  for lifetime in segment.lifetimes.iter() {
 1553                      if comma {
 1554                          try!(self.word_space(","))
 1555                      }
 1556                      try!(self.print_lifetime(lifetime));
 1557                      comma = true;
 1558                  }
 1559  
 1560                  if !segment.types.is_empty() {
 1561                      if comma {
 1562                          try!(self.word_space(","))
 1563                      }
 1564                      try!(self.commasep(
 1565                          Inconsistent,
 1566                          segment.types.as_slice(),
 1567                          |s, ty| s.print_type_ref(ty)));
 1568                  }
 1569  
 1570                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ">"))
 1571              }
 1572          }
 1573          Ok(())
 1574      }

 1587      pub fn print_pat(&mut self, pat: &ast::Pat) -> IoResult<()> {
 1588          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(pat.span.lo));
 1589          try!(self.ann.pre(self, NodePat(pat)));
 1590          /* Pat isn't normalized, but the beauty of it
 1591           is that it doesn't matter */
 1592          match pat.node {
 1593              ast::PatWild => try!(word(&mut self.s, "_")),
 1594              ast::PatWildMulti => try!(word(&mut self.s, "..")),
 1595              ast::PatIdent(binding_mode, ref path, sub) => {
 1596                  match binding_mode {
 1597                      ast::BindByRef(mutbl) => {
 1598                          try!(self.word_nbsp("ref"));
 1599                          try!(self.print_mutability(mutbl));
 1600                      }
 1601                      ast::BindByValue(ast::MutImmutable) => {}
 1602                      ast::BindByValue(ast::MutMutable) => {
 1603                          try!(self.word_nbsp("mut"));
 1604                      }
 1605                  }
 1606                  try!(self.print_path(path, true));
 1607                  match sub {
 1608                      Some(p) => {
 1609                          try!(word(&mut self.s, "@"));
 1610                          try!(self.print_pat(p));
 1611                      }
 1612                      None => ()
 1613                  }
 1614              }
 1615              ast::PatEnum(ref path, ref args_) => {
 1616                  try!(self.print_path(path, true));
 1617                  match *args_ {
 1618                      None => try!(word(&mut self.s, "(..)")),
 1619                      Some(ref args) => {
 1620                          if !args.is_empty() {
 1621                              try!(self.popen());
 1622                              try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent, args.as_slice(),
 1623                                                |s, &p| s.print_pat(p)));
 1624                              try!(self.pclose());
 1625                          }
 1626                      }
 1627                  }
 1628              }
 1629              ast::PatStruct(ref path, ref fields, etc) => {
 1630                  try!(self.print_path(path, true));
 1631                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "{"));
 1632                  try!(self.commasep_cmnt(
 1633                      Consistent, fields.as_slice(),
 1634                      |s, f| {
 1635                          try!(s.cbox(indent_unit));
 1636                          try!(s.print_ident(f.ident));
 1637                          try!(s.word_space(":"));
 1638                          try!(s.print_pat(f.pat));
 1639                          s.end()
 1640                      },
 1641                      |f| f.pat.span));
 1642                  if etc {
 1643                      if fields.len() != 0u { try!(self.word_space(",")); }
 1644                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ".."));
 1645                  }
 1646                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "}"));
 1647              }
 1648              ast::PatTup(ref elts) => {
 1649                  try!(self.popen());
 1650                  try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent,
 1651                                     elts.as_slice(),
 1652                                     |s, &p| s.print_pat(p)));
 1653                  if elts.len() == 1 {
 1654                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
 1655                  }
 1656                  try!(self.pclose());
 1657              }
 1658              ast::PatUniq(inner) => {
 1659                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "~"));
 1660                  try!(self.print_pat(inner));
 1661              }
 1662              ast::PatRegion(inner) => {
 1663                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "&"));
 1664                  try!(self.print_pat(inner));
 1665              }
 1666              ast::PatLit(e) => try!(self.print_expr(e)),
 1667              ast::PatRange(begin, end) => {
 1668                  try!(self.print_expr(begin));
 1669                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1670                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ".."));
 1671                  try!(self.print_expr(end));
 1672              }
 1673              ast::PatVec(ref before, slice, ref after) => {
 1674                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
 1675                  try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent,
 1676                                     before.as_slice(),
 1677                                     |s, &p| s.print_pat(p)));
 1678                  for &p in slice.iter() {
 1679                      if !before.is_empty() { try!(self.word_space(",")); }
 1680                      match *p {
 1681                          ast::Pat { node: ast::PatWildMulti, .. } => {
 1682                              // this case is handled by print_pat
 1683                          }
 1684                          _ => try!(word(&mut self.s, "..")),
 1685                      }
 1686                      try!(self.print_pat(p));
 1687                      if !after.is_empty() { try!(self.word_space(",")); }
 1688                  }
 1689                  try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent,
 1690                                     after.as_slice(),
 1691                                     |s, &p| s.print_pat(p)));
 1692                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
 1693              }
 1694          }
 1695          self.ann.post(self, NodePat(pat))
 1696      }

 1738      pub fn print_fn_args(&mut self, decl: &ast::FnDecl,
 1739                           opt_explicit_self: Option<ast::ExplicitSelf_>)
 1740          -> IoResult<()> {
 1741          // It is unfortunate to duplicate the commasep logic, but we want the
 1742          // self type and the args all in the same box.
 1743          try!(self.rbox(0u, Inconsistent));
 1744          let mut first = true;
 1745          for &explicit_self in opt_explicit_self.iter() {
 1746              let m = match explicit_self {
 1747                  ast::SelfStatic => ast::MutImmutable,
 1748                  _ => match decl.inputs.get(0).pat.node {
 1749                      ast::PatIdent(ast::BindByValue(m), _, _) => m,
 1750                      _ => ast::MutImmutable
 1751                  }
 1752              };
 1753              first = !try!(self.print_explicit_self(explicit_self, m));
 1754          }
 1755  
 1756          // HACK(eddyb) ignore the separately printed self argument.
 1757          let args = if first {
 1758              decl.inputs.as_slice()
 1759          } else {
 1760              decl.inputs.slice_from(1)
 1761          };
 1762  
 1763          for arg in args.iter() {
 1764              if first { first = false; } else { try!(self.word_space(",")); }
 1765              try!(self.print_arg(arg));
 1766          }
 1767  
 1768          self.end()
 1769      }

 1860      pub fn print_generics(&mut self,
 1861                            generics: &ast::Generics) -> IoResult<()> {
 1862          let total = generics.lifetimes.len() + generics.ty_params.len();
 1863          if total > 0 {
 1864              try!(word(&mut self.s, "<"));
 1865  
 1866              let mut ints = Vec::new();
 1867              for i in range(0u, total) {
 1868                  ints.push(i);
 1869              }
 1870  
 1871              try!(self.commasep(
 1872                  Inconsistent, ints.as_slice(),
 1873                  |s, &idx| {
 1874                      if idx < generics.lifetimes.len() {
 1875                          let lifetime = generics.lifetimes.get(idx);
 1876                          s.print_lifetime(lifetime)
 1877                      } else {
 1878                          let idx = idx - generics.lifetimes.len();
 1879                          let param = generics.ty_params.get(idx);
 1880                          try!(s.print_ident(param.ident));
 1881                          try!(s.print_bounds(&param.bounds, false));
 1882                          match param.default {
 1883                              Some(default) => {
 1884                                  try!(space(&mut s.s));
 1885                                  try!(s.word_space("="));
 1886                                  s.print_type(default)
 1887                              }
 1888                              _ => Ok(())
 1889                          }
 1890                      }
 1891                  }));
 1892              word(&mut self.s, ">")
 1893          } else {
 1894              Ok(())
 1895          }
 1896      }

 1921      pub fn print_view_path(&mut self, vp: &ast::ViewPath) -> IoResult<()> {
 1922          match vp.node {
 1923              ast::ViewPathSimple(ident, ref path, _) => {

 1958      pub fn print_view_item(&mut self, item: &ast::ViewItem) -> IoResult<()> {

 1983      }

 1998      pub fn print_arg(&mut self, input: &ast::Arg) -> IoResult<()> {

 2022      pub fn print_ty_fn(&mut self,
 2023                         opt_abis: Option<AbiSet>,
 2024                         opt_sigil: Option<ast::Sigil>,
 2025                         opt_region: &Option<ast::Lifetime>,
 2026                         purity: ast::Purity,
 2027                         onceness: ast::Onceness,
 2028                         decl: &ast::FnDecl,
 2029                         id: Option<ast::Ident>,
 2030                         opt_bounds: &Option<OwnedSlice<ast::TyParamBound>>,
 2031                         generics: Option<&ast::Generics>,
 2032                         opt_explicit_self: Option<ast::ExplicitSelf_>)
 2033          -> IoResult<()> {
 2034          try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
 2035  
 2036          // Duplicates the logic in `print_fn_header_info()`.  This is because that
 2037          // function prints the sigil in the wrong place.  That should be fixed.
 2038          if opt_sigil == Some(ast::OwnedSigil) && onceness == ast::Once {
 2039              try!(word(&mut self.s, "proc"));
 2040          } else if opt_sigil == Some(ast::BorrowedSigil) {
 2041              try!(self.print_extern_opt_abis(opt_abis));
 2042              for lifetime in opt_region.iter() {
 2043                  try!(self.print_lifetime(lifetime));
 2044              }
 2045              try!(self.print_purity(purity));
 2046              try!(self.print_onceness(onceness));
 2047          } else {
 2048              try!(self.print_opt_abis_and_extern_if_nondefault(opt_abis));
 2049              try!(self.print_opt_sigil(opt_sigil));
 2050              try!(self.print_opt_lifetime(opt_region));
 2051              try!(self.print_purity(purity));
 2052              try!(self.print_onceness(onceness));
 2053              try!(word(&mut self.s, "fn"));
 2054          }
 2055  
 2056          match id {
 2057              Some(id) => {
 2058                  try!(word(&mut self.s, " "));
 2059                  try!(self.print_ident(id));
 2060              }
 2061              _ => ()
 2062          }
 2063  
 2064          if opt_sigil != Some(ast::BorrowedSigil) {
 2065              opt_bounds.as_ref().map(|bounds| self.print_bounds(bounds, true));
 2066          }
 2067  
 2068          match generics { Some(g) => try!(self.print_generics(g)), _ => () }
 2069          try!(zerobreak(&mut self.s));
 2070  
 2071          if opt_sigil == Some(ast::BorrowedSigil) {
 2072              try!(word(&mut self.s, "|"));
 2073          } else {
 2074              try!(self.popen());
 2075          }
 2076  
 2077          try!(self.print_fn_args(decl, opt_explicit_self));
 2078  
 2079          if opt_sigil == Some(ast::BorrowedSigil) {
 2080              try!(word(&mut self.s, "|"));
 2081  
 2082              opt_bounds.as_ref().map(|bounds| self.print_bounds(bounds, true));
 2083          } else {
 2084              if decl.variadic {
 2085                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ", ..."));
 2086              }
 2087              try!(self.pclose());
 2088          }
 2089  
 2090          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(decl.output.span.lo));
 2091  
 2092          match decl.output.node {
 2093              ast::TyNil => {}

 2106  
 2107          self.end()

 2110      pub fn maybe_print_trailing_comment(&mut self, span: codemap::Span,
 2111                                          next_pos: Option<BytePos>)
 2112          -> IoResult<()> {
 2113          let cm = match self.cm {
 2114              Some(cm) => cm,
 2115              _ => return Ok(())
 2116          };
 2117          match self.next_comment() {
 2118              Some(ref cmnt) => {
 2119                  if (*cmnt).style != comments::Trailing { return Ok(()) }
 2120                  let span_line = cm.lookup_char_pos(span.hi);
 2121                  let comment_line = cm.lookup_char_pos((*cmnt).pos);
 2122                  let mut next = (*cmnt).pos + BytePos(1);
 2123                  match next_pos { None => (), Some(p) => next = p }
 2124                  if span.hi < (*cmnt).pos && (*cmnt).pos < next &&
 2125                      span_line.line == comment_line.line {
 2126                          try!(self.print_comment(cmnt));
 2127                          self.cur_cmnt_and_lit.cur_cmnt += 1u;
 2128                      }
 2129              }
 2130              _ => ()
 2131          }
 2132          Ok(())
 2133      }

 2135      pub fn print_remaining_comments(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> {
 2136          // If there aren't any remaining comments, then we need to manually
 2137          // make sure there is a line break at the end.
 2138          if self.next_comment().is_none() {
 2139              try!(hardbreak(&mut self.s));
 2140          }
 2141          loop {
 2142              match self.next_comment() {
 2143                  Some(ref cmnt) => {
 2144                      try!(self.print_comment(cmnt));
 2145                      self.cur_cmnt_and_lit.cur_cmnt += 1u;
 2146                  }
 2147                  _ => break
 2148              }
 2149          }
 2150          Ok(())
 2151      }

 2153      pub fn print_literal(&mut self, lit: &ast::Lit) -> IoResult<()> {
 2154          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(lit.span.lo));
 2155          match self.next_lit(lit.span.lo) {
 2156              Some(ref ltrl) => {
 2157                  return word(&mut self.s, (*ltrl).lit);
 2158              }
 2159              _ => ()
 2160          }
 2161          match lit.node {
 2162              ast::LitStr(ref st, style) => self.print_string(st.get(), style),
 2163              ast::LitChar(ch) => {
 2164                  let mut res = ~"'";
 2165                  char::from_u32(ch).unwrap().escape_default(|c| res.push_char(c));
 2166                  res.push_char('\'');
 2167                  word(&mut self.s, res)
 2168              }
 2169              ast::LitInt(i, t) => {
 2170                  word(&mut self.s, format!("{}{}", i, ast_util::int_ty_to_str(t)))
 2171              }
 2172              ast::LitUint(u, t) => {
 2173                  word(&mut self.s, format!("{}{}", u, ast_util::uint_ty_to_str(t)))
 2174              }
 2175              ast::LitIntUnsuffixed(i) => {
 2176                  word(&mut self.s, format!("{}", i))
 2177              }
 2178              ast::LitFloat(ref f, t) => {
 2179                  word(&mut self.s, f.get() + ast_util::float_ty_to_str(t))
 2180              }
 2181              ast::LitFloatUnsuffixed(ref f) => word(&mut self.s, f.get()),
 2182              ast::LitNil => word(&mut self.s, "()"),
 2183              ast::LitBool(val) => {
 2184                  if val { word(&mut self.s, "true") } else { word(&mut self.s, "false") }
 2185              }
 2186              ast::LitBinary(ref arr) => {
 2187                  try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
 2188                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
 2189                  try!(self.commasep_cmnt(Inconsistent, arr.as_slice(),
 2190                                          |s, u| word(&mut s.s, format!("{}", *u)),
 2191                                          |_| lit.span));
 2192                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
 2193                  self.end()
 2194              }

 2228      pub fn print_comment(&mut self,
 2229                           cmnt: &comments::Comment) -> IoResult<()> {
 2230          match cmnt.style {
 2231              comments::Mixed => {
 2232                  assert_eq!(cmnt.lines.len(), 1u);
 2233                  try!(zerobreak(&mut self.s));
 2234                  try!(word(&mut self.s, *cmnt.lines.get(0)));
 2235                  zerobreak(&mut self.s)
 2236              }
 2237              comments::Isolated => {
 2238                  try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
 2239                  for line in cmnt.lines.iter() {
 2240                      // Don't print empty lines because they will end up as trailing
 2241                      // whitespace
 2242                      if !line.is_empty() {
 2243                          try!(word(&mut self.s, *line));
 2244                      }
 2245                      try!(hardbreak(&mut self.s));
 2246                  }
 2247                  Ok(())
 2248              }
 2249              comments::Trailing => {
 2250                  try!(word(&mut self.s, " "));

 2252                      try!(word(&mut self.s, *cmnt.lines.get(0)));
 2253                      hardbreak(&mut self.s)
 2254                  } else {
 2255                      try!(self.ibox(0u));
 2256                      for line in cmnt.lines.iter() {
 2257                          if !line.is_empty() {
 2258                              try!(word(&mut self.s, *line));
 2259                          }
 2260                          try!(hardbreak(&mut self.s));
 2261                      }
 2262                      self.end()
 2263                  }
 2264              }
 2265              comments::BlankLine => {
 2266                  // We need to do at least one, possibly two hardbreaks.
 2267                  let is_semi = match self.s.last_token() {
 2268                      pp::String(s, _) => ";" == s,
 2269                      _ => false
 2270                  };

 2273                  }
 2274                  hardbreak(&mut self.s)
 2275              }
 2276          }
 2277      }
